<h1> Description: The index page is usually the first page that a user sees when he/she visits a website. This is how our index page should look like: </h1>

This is a web page contains three sections:

<b> Header <br>
Content <br>
Footer <br></b>

Header: This is the first section of the webpage and it contains the
<b><em> “The Online Cloth Shopping Store” </b></em> as a website name and navigation links to login and signup page.

Content: This section has two parts banner image with a Shop Now button over it and item category listing section.

Footer: The footer contains text <b><em>“Copyright @ The Online Cloth Shopping Store All Rights Reserved | Contact Us: +91 80000 00000 ” </em></b>.

Approach:
Here is a starter template:HTML
<h2> Index.html </h2>

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
<!-- The page has a title The Online Cloth Shopping Store -->
<title>Online cloth shopping Store</title>
<!---- External css file index.css placed in the folder css is linked-->
<link href="css/index.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/>
</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>
```



In the above template, the page title is mentioned as <b><em> “The Online Cloth Shopping Store” </b></em> and an external CSS file ```style.css``` in linked.

The basic CSS in ``Style.css`` would be

```css
body{
width: 100%;
height: 100%;
margin: 0;
}
a{
text-decoration: none;
background-color: transparent;
color:#ededed;
}
```

##

<b> <h1>Header</h1> </b>

1. Inside the ```<body>``` create a div (using ```<div>``` tag) with class header assigned to Class header would contain the following

```css
background-color: #000;
color:#fff;
border-color:#080808;
min-height:50px;
border:1px solid transparent;
```

##

2. Inside the div with class header, create a div with class inner-header which will free some space on the sides of the header.
Class inner-header would contain the following

```css
width:80%;
margin:auto;
```

##

3. Div with class ```inner-header``` will contain ```three``` div

##

4. First div element will have class ```logo``` with content <b><em> “The Online Cloth Shopping Store” </b></em> which will be a Class logo will contain the following

```css
float: right;
font-size:14px;
height: 50px;
padding: 15px 15px;
font-size:16px;
font-weight: bold;
```

##

5. Second div element will have content ```Sign up``` and third div element will have content ```Login``` with same class ```header-link``` to both div elements. Both Signup and login will be links.Class ``header-link`` will contain the following

```css
float: right;
font-size:14px;
height: 50px;
padding: 15px 15px;
font-size:16px;
font-weight: bold;
```

##

6. This marks the end to inner-header div element and header div Now, you have made the header of the web page7.Start div tag with Class content will have the following

```css
min-height:600px;
```

##

7. Div element with class content will contain div element with class banner-

```css
padding-bottom: 50px;
margin-bottom: 20px;
text-align: center;
color: #f8f8f8;
background: url(image_name) no-repeat center;
background-size: cover;
```

Class banner-image will have the following

##

8. Div element with class banner-image will have one div element with class inner-banner-

Class inner-banner-image will have the following

```css
padding-top:12%;
width:80%;
margin:auto;
```
##

9. Start a div element inside the div element with class inner-banner-image with class

Class banner_content will have the following

```css
position: relative;
padding-top: 6%;
padding-bottom: 6%;
overflow:hidden;
margin-bottom: 12%;
background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
max-width: 660px;
```
##

10. Add H1 tag inside this div element with content <b>``“We sell ”``</b>.
##
11. Add p tag with content <b>``“Flat 40% OFF on premium brands”``</b>.
##
12. Add a link after p Link will contain class button.

```css
color: #fff;
background-color:#c9302c;
border-color: #ac2925;
box-shadow: inset 0 3px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 125);
padding: 10px 16px;
font-size: 18px;
border-radius: 6px;
```

Class button will have the following

##

13. Close all the div elements till the div element with class banner_image. Now, you have made the banner.

##

14. After writing the above HTML and CSS code, Web page should look like this:


![Banner](images/readme/banner.png)

<b> <h1>Content</h1></b>

##

15. Start a div element with class This class will enclose the images and their div elements.

##

16. Class container will contain the following

```css
width:90%;
margin:auto;
overflow:hidden;
```

##

17. Start a div element inside the container div element with class

```css
width:30%;
display: block;
padding: 4px;
margin-bottom: 20px;
line-height: 1.42857143;
background-color: #fff;
border: 1px solid #ddd;
border-radius: 4px;
float:left;
margin-left:1%;
```

Class items will have the following

##

18. Start the anchor All the next HTML elements will be inside the anchor tag.

##

19. Start the image Class thumbnail is assigned to img tag.
Class thumbnail will contain the following
```css
    width: 100%;
```

##

20. Start a div element after image tag with .Class caption will contain the following

```css
color:#000;
padding:0px 10px 10px;
font-weight: bold;
text-align: center;
```
##

21. Add H2 tag with content “Watches” and paragraph tag with content “Original watches from the best brands.”.

```html
<div class="items">
<a href="#">
<img src="img/1.jpg" alt="" class="thumbnail">
<div class="caption">
<h2>Cameras</h2>
<p>Choose among the best available in the world.</p>
</div>
</a>
</div>
```

Close the caption div element, anchor tag and items The HTML code will be:

##

22. Replicate this div element with class items and HTML content inside it two IT will create three div elements. Change the content and paragraph for other two elements.

##

23. Close the container div element and content div element

##

24. After writing the above HTML and CSS code, your page should look like this:

![Body Content](images/readme/Content.png)

##

25. One Image showing overall website look with all products

<b> <h1>Footer</h1> </b>

##

26. Start the footer

Footer element will have the following

##

27. Start a div element with the class This class is already used before.

##

28. Add a paragraph tag with content in Content is “Copyright © Online Cloth Store. All Rights Reserved | Contact Us: +91 80000 00000”.
##

29. Close the container div element, footer
##

30. Close the body tag and HTML
##

31. Hence, your web page is

